Classification.Comment: The c.4359delA pathogenic mutation, located in coding exon 12 of the BRCA1 gene, results from a deletion of one nucleotide at nucleotide position 4359, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon (p.V1454Yfs*2). This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. As such, this alteration is interpreted as a disease-causing mutation.
